         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">8 April 1870 ¶  ¶ [Director recommends that the Inspr of Forests ¶ William Ferguson. ¶  ¶ may be placed under the Lands Dept with a view of commencing an inspection of the principal forests of this Co...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.04.08<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John MacPherson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 3559, vol. 1870 W, VPRS 1168/P inward correspondence registers, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">Trans 24.1.94. To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">Reg only note needed</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">See also M to J. MacPherson, 25 March 1870.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">Subsequent letter Z71/7867. Follow up chain.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>8 April 1870</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[Director recommends that the Inspr of Forests<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">William Ferguson.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>may be placed under the Lands Dept with a view of commencing an inspection of the principal forests of this Colony<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">See notes to W. Odgers to M, 24 March 1870 for the text of an enclosed letter to William Ferguson. The letter<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">from Odgers<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">to Ferguson included '</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">it would be well for you to hold yourself in readiness to actively engage in the work of Inspection of Forests as soon as suitable weather sets in'.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>It is probable that M knew the content of the letter and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">may have acted when the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">weather at the end of March and the first week of April was</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>generally</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'dry and warm'</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and 'warm and sultry' (Government Astronomers reports,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-style: italic; color: #0070C0; ">Argus</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">, 4 April 1870, p. 5 and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-style: italic; color: #0070C0; ">Argus</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">11 April, p. 5).</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">letter was referred to the Commissioner of Crown Lands on 12 April 1870 and returned to the Chief Secretary's Department on 21 April.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>]</p>
         </div>
